Specifically, the domain descriptor grammar (the DOMAINS environment
variable syntax) and the public configuration surface (environment
variable names where applicable) are preserved to enable existing
https-portal users to migrate with minimal changes. The parser, renderer,
and runtime have been rewritten from scratch in TypeScript against
Caddy as the underlying HTTPS server.

caddy-portal embeds and redistributes the Caddy web server
(https://caddyserver.com), which is licensed under the Apache License 2.0.
